olic Churches]] at Nicaea ([[\u0130znik]], Turkey) to mark the 1,700th anniversary of the [[First Council of Nicaea|Council of Nicaea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonwealmagazine.org/blog/nicea-iii-2025 |title=Nicea III in 2025? |publisher=Commonweal Magazine |date=2014-05-30 |accessdate=2015-11-12}}</ref>\n*[[World population]] is expected to reach 8 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.natureworldnews.com/articles/2447/20130614/un-world-population-report-predicts-8-billion-people-2025-11.htm|title=UN World Population Report Predicts 8 Billion People by 2025, 11 billion by 2100|first=|last=NatureWorldNews|date=June 14, 2013|publisher=|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n* The [[European Space Agency]] plans to begin mining the [[moon]] for natural resources by this date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/01/22/europe/mining-on-moon-trnd/index.html|title=The European Space Agency plans to start mining for natural resources on the moon|first=Lauren|last=Kent|date=January 22, 2019|publisher=CNN|accessdate=January 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Norway]] plans to ban the sale of all new diesel and petrol cars by this year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://qz.com/1341155/nine-countries-say-they-will-ban-internal-combustion-engines-none-have-a-law-to-do-so/|title=Nine countries say they\u2019ll ban internal combustion engines|date=June 6, 2019|publisher=|via=qz.com}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[21st century in fiction]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2025}}\n[[Category:2025| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Short description|Year}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Year dab|2025}}\n{{Year nav|2025}}\n{{C21 year in topic}}\n{{Year article header|2025}}\n\n== Predicted and scheduled events ==\n\n* [[January 1]] &ndash; The American [[Federal Aviation Administration|FAA]] will have been implementing a new system of [[Global Positioning System|GPS]] called [[Next Generation Air Transportation System|NextGen]] that will be fully functional by this year, alongside that, [[1929 in literature|books]], [[1929 in film|films]], and other works published in 1929 will enter the public domain..<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.nytimes.com/2009/11/17/science/17air.html?pagewanted=all | work=The New York Times | first=Guy | last=Gugliotta | title=An Air-Traffic Upgrade to Improve Travel by Plane | date=November 17, 2009}}</ref>\n* [[May]]&ndash;[[October]] &ndash; [[Expo 2025]] will be held in [[Osaka]], [[Japan]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://japan-forward.com/osaka-is-world-expo-2025-host/|title=Osaka Is World Expo 2025 Host {{!}} JAPAN Forward|date=2018-11-23|work=Japan Forward|access-date=2018-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref>\n\n===Date unknown===\n<!-- Please do not add claims by SpaceX that this will be the year humans land on Mars, as SpaceX is not an encyclopedic source -->\n\n* Both ''[[Voyager 1]]'' and ''[[Voyager 2]]'' space probes have sufficient electrical power to operate their [[Transmitter|radio transmitters]] until at least 2025.<ref>{{cite web|url = http://voyager.jpl.nasa.gov/spacecraft/spacecraftlife.html|title = Voyager \u2013 Spacecraft \u2013 Spacecraft Lifetime|accessdate = November 4, 2007|date = 2003-01-14|publisher = [[NASA]] [[Jet Propulsion Laboratory]]| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20071027080026/http://voyager.jpl.nasa.gov/spacecraft/spacecraftlife.html| archivedate=October 27, 2007| url-status= live}}</ref>\n* Planned ecumenical meeting of the [[Eastern Orthodox Church|Orthodox]] and [[Catholic Church|Catholic Churches]] at Nicaea ([[\u0130znik]], Turkey) to mark the 1,700th anniversary of the [[First Council of Nicaea|Council of Nicaea]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.commonwealmagazine.org/blog/nicea-iii-2025 |title=Nicea III in 2025? |publisher=Commonweal Magazine |date=2014-05-30 |accessdate=2015-11-12}}</ref>\n*[[World population]] is expected to reach 8 billion.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.natureworldnews.com/articles/2447/20130614/un-world-population-report-predicts-8-billion-people-2025-11.htm|title=UN World Population Report Predicts 8 Billion People by 2025, 11 billion by 2100|first=|last=NatureWorldNews|date=June 14, 2013|publisher=|accessdate=October 30, 2016}}</ref>\n* The [[European Space Agency]] plans to begin mining the [[moon]] for natural resources by this date.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2019/01/22/europe/mining-on-moon-trnd/index.html|title=The European Space Agency plans to start mining for natural resources on the moon|first=Lauren|last=Kent|date=January 22, 2019|publisher=CNN|accessdate=January 23, 2019}}</ref>\n* [[Norway]] plans to ban the sale of all new diesel and petrol cars by this year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://qz.com/1341155/nine-countries-say-they-will-ban-internal-combustion-engines-none-have-a-law-to-do-so/|title=Nine countries say they\u2019ll ban internal combustion engines|date=June 6, 2019|publisher=|via=qz.com}}</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[21st century in fiction]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2025}}\n[[Category:2025| ]]\n", "name_user": "Googgoollman7777", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200ePredicted and scheduled events:Deleted extra punctuation mark.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/2025"}
